value.0: With a serrated blade and heavy maille, these bouncers are not to be trifled with.
This is a settlement guard insignia for the guard templates.

Value.value: Well, well, well. New blood, eh? I've half a mind to bust yer' bones just for gettin' down here.
But I'm in a generous mood. Prove yer' worth and maybe there'll be more work for you.
And maybe.. just maybe, you'll get to see what's past this door.
Sneak into their estate and bring back anything you find that might pique my interest. Any word of this to anyone and yer' toast. Got it?
There's a merchant family in East Southport called the Matelizis. They've got more money than sense.
What you back here for empty handed? Go to Palazzo Matelizi and find something good!
Nice work.. Now for the real challenge. Go through the sewers and find your way through to the Undercity. Talk to one of my associates and tell 'em Chancey sent ya'.
What you waiting for? Find the Undercity and tell 'em Chancey sent you. Best way's through the sewers.

value.0:
Universal Template for settlement Scout Guard.

You may change appearances of items or change weapon types, but make sure all items have the same properties afterward. Do not change stats on the base creature, either. This is important for fairness across the board. Do not give them any additional accessories beyond what is visible: armor, cloak, helmet, shield, weapon. They don't have to have all of these items equipped, but do not give them more than that.

Seeking weapons are the pride of those who prefer to face their enemy at a distance. Crafted of ebony and enchanted by ancient magical enhancements of the Elemental Plane of Air, these weapons cause a momentary tunnel of wind as the projectile is fired, causing the weapon to rarely miss and connect with the target at a much higher velocity.
This is a settlement guard insignia for the guard templates.

Value.value: What's that ye be mumblin' about? Speak up, or take it outside and settle it like a proper seafarer.

value.0:
A flamboyant tiefling bard strums a lute with unsettling enthusiasm,
their crimson skin reflecting the flickering torchlight.

A fine stringed instrument, a lute is very mobile, and as such, a favorite of traveling minstrels everywhere.  It has a pleasing sound, as the strings musical vibrations echo in the hollow wooden chamber and reverberate.

Value.value: Another round for the loveliest scoundrels in Southport! Tonight, we sing of shadows and secrets!

value.0: A wizened gnome in tattered robes hunches over a table, surrounded by vials of bubbling liquids.

Value.value: Got a particular itch that needs scratching? I might have just the potion... *The gnome's eyes gleam with avarice*
Not much of a rind on you...

A cloaked figure with shadowed eyes mutters to themself,
occasionally clutching a pouch of shimmering dust.
This helmet gives the wearer agility in facing a single adversary, his movements fluid and prepared for anything his opponent may throw at him.

Value.value: Silence! I'm conducting a very important transaction here!

value.0:
Morgug is a hulking half-orc with tusks that curl back from his bottom jaw, perpetually stained a faint yellow from years of chewing on pipeweed. 

Despite his imposing stature, his single good eye holds a surprising warmth, often crinkling at the corners when a particularly outrageous rumor is shared. He moves with surprising grace for his size, weaving between patrons with mugs balanced precariously on a massive, scarred hand.
A hooded figure with a perpetual cough lingers near the front of the bar, their gloved hand always near a bulging pouch.
This helmet gives the wearer agility in facing a single adversary, his movements fluid and prepared for anything his opponent may throw at him.

Value.value: Psst! You want to sample some of the good stuff?
